From: syzkaller per-vm-debug-streams patch
Subject: vm: per-VM debug streams (file + TCP) for multi-device debug runs

Adds a -debug-streams flag to syz-manager that routes each VM's
OutputMerger output to a per-VM log file under <workdir>/debug/
and a per-VM TCP listener on 127.0.0.1:6000+index, instead of
the legacy shared os.Stdout tee. Unlike -debug, the new flag
does NOT clamp count=1, so multiple devices/VMs can run in
parallel while keeping per-device debug visibility.

See per-vm-debug-streams.analysis for design notes.

---

